DC REST Swiss API documentation version 11.0.4

https://<tenantId>.<partner-domain-name>/2

Doc Cirrus REST API /2, /3

This file documents all releases of the externally available Doc Cirrus inSuite REST API. It provides a complete set of allowed resources and the methods to access them.

Useful resources

Changelog

RAML Doc

JS Schema

Endpoint versions

/2 Low-level API

Here fine grained control of many resources in Doc Cirrus are made available.

/3 Public API

Here the resources do not need any authentication. Currently only for VoIP / PBX integration.

Introduction

Types

Types are Javascript Types.

  • “Date” (also written “date”) is always a “datetime” - "2019-05-28T12:26:00.000Z" as known from other languages like Java.
  • Number is a double float, but can be denoted as an integer.

The other structures are standard Javascript Object Notation (JSON) structures:

  • String
  • Array
  • Object

Notes:

  • For multi-tenant systems, the REST server determines which tenant is being addressed by the tenantId in the hostname that the request is sent to.
  • Regular Expression operators are available for all "string" type parameters. Use
  • <paramname>_regex (matches /^val/) OR <paramname>_iregex (matches /val/, "i")

API "Activity" Endpoints:

  • The Doc Cirrus workflow requires that a valid contract be created, before another activity can be created. The contract and activities are related by their location, case folder and patient references.
  • When creating a '0102' type PUBLIC contract, the system will create a DIAGNOSIS of type 'UUU' automatically. This is because specialists such as radiologists, or laboratories only analyse without diagnosing the patient in some situations.
  • Different kinds of utility are specified through the subType field, which can be used in the other Activity endpoints for user specified categorisation.
  • Contract type activities have restrictions on where they can be moved (e.g. changing case folder, or changing the time of the activity). Illegal changes are cancelled by the system and an error is returned.

Activity endpoints are the following:

  • labdata
  • complexprescription
  • contract
  • assistive
  • meddata
  • medication
  • treatment
  • diagnosis
  • invoice
  • utility

API "Simple Activity" Endpoints:

  • Simple activities all have a common Schema.
  • You can POST, or PUT them in the usual manner( as mentioned below ).
  • If requesting only simple activities of a specific type, the caller must always add a query parameter to the REST interface in the following manner: /2/simple_activity?actType=THERAPY

Simple activity endpoints are always up to date in the RAML Schema, and currently the following:

  • THERAPY
  • CAVE
  • HISTORY
  • EXTERNAL
  • FINDING
  • PREVENTION
  • PROCEDERE
  • REMINDER
  • CREDITNOTE
  • WARNING1
  • WARNING2
  • COMMUNICATION
  • PROCESS
  • CONTACT
  • FROMPATIENT
  • FROMPATIENTMEDIA
  • TELECONSULT
  • MEDICATIONPLAN
  • GRAVIDOGRAMM
  • DOCLETTERDIAGNOSIS
  • DOCLETTER
  • PRIVPRESCR
  • PUBPRESCR
  • FORM
  • THERAPYSTEP

Operators

Search parameters also allows operators.

  • DCQuery.GT_OPERATOR = 'gt'
  • DCQuery.LT_OPERATOR = 'lt'
  • DCQuery.EQ_OPERATOR = 'eq'
  • DCQuery.EQ_OPERATOR_FOR_NUMBER = 'eqNumber'
  • DCQuery.EQ_BOOL_OPERATOR = 'bool_eq'
  • DCQuery.EQDATE_OPERATOR = 'eqDate'
  • DCQuery.GTE_OPERATOR = 'gte'
  • DCQuery.LTE_OPERATOR = 'lte'
  • DCQuery.IREGEX_OPERATOR = 'iregex'
  • DCQuery.REGEX_OPERATOR = 'regex'
  • DCQuery.IN_OPERATOR = 'in'
  • DCQuery.ENUM_OPERATOR = 'enum'
  • DCQuery.NOT_IREGEX_OPERATOR = 'notiregex'
  • DCQuery.NIN_OPERATOR = 'nin'

Testing the API:

  • Create a user for REST access in your tenant or appliance. (e.g. "user", "password")
  • Create a testfile for an endpoint, by copying a response JSON from this documentation and saving it (name it e.g. "test_data.json").
  • Then make the REST call. The following example uses the command line utility "curl".
  • curl -k -X POST -H "Content-Type:application/json" --user user:"password" https://<host_address>/2/diagnosis -d @test_data.json
  • The Doc Cirrus test cases demonstrate on a high level the kind of algorithm you need to implement to add activities to the system:

/2/assistive

Assistive type activities represent 'Hilfsmittel', e.g. assId '100.99.0.2990'. These may be prescribed from a catalog. The REST API currently does not allow access to catalogs, and it is up to the caller to enter the correct prescriptions (assId code and descriptions).

/2/assistive get post

get

Get a list of assistives.

post

Add a new assistive.

get /2/assistive

Get a list of assistives.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: status, subType, timestamp, patientId, locationId, mirrorCaseFolderType, formId, formVersion, caseFolderId, patientName, assDescription, assDose, assPrescPeriod, code. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • status: (string)
  • subType: (string)
  • timestamp: (date)
  • patientId: (string)
  • locationId: (string)
  • mirrorCaseFolderType: (string)
  • formId: (string)
  • formVersion: (string)
  • caseFolderId: (string)
  • patientName: (string)
  • assDescription: (string)
  • assDose: (string)
  • assPrescPeriod: (string)
  • code: (string)

HTTP status code 400

Body

Type: application/json

Secured by basic

Secured by oauth2

Headers

  • Authorization: (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

Secured by JWT

Headers

  • Authorization: required (string)

    X-DC-App-Name

        "page": null,
        "replyCode": 200
  },
  "data": [
     "54be764fc404c1d77a286d4d"
   ]
 }

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

/2/assistive/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a assistive

get

Get the assistive with assistiveId = {assistiveId}

put

Update a specific assistive using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

delete

Delete a specific assistive.

Collection of available audits via REST /2.

get

Get a list of audits.

post

Add a new audit.

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Example:

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: . Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'

Secured by basic

Secured by oauth2

Headers

  • Authorization: (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

/2/audit/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a audit

get

Get the audit with auditId = {auditId}

put

Update a specific audit using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

/2/basecontact

Provides access to the basecontacts collection. Query documents by _id, officialNo and bsnrs like /2/basecontact/?officialNo=999999900

/2/basecontact get post

get

Get a list of basecontacts.

post

Add a new basecontact.

get /2/basecontact

Get a list of basecontacts.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: baseContactType, firstname, lastname, officialNo. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • baseContactType: (string)
  • firstname: (string)
  • lastname: (string)
  • officialNo: (string)

HTTP status code 400

Body

Type: application/json

Secured by basic

Secured by oauth2

Headers

  • Authorization: (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

/2/basecontact/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a basecontact

get

Get the basecontact with basecontactId = {basecontactId}

put

Update a specific basecontact using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

delete

Delete a specific basecontact.

get /2/basecontact/{_id}

Get the basecontact with basecontactId = {basecontactId}

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • _id: required (string)

/2/billing

Only for MTS systems. It gathers some information in master tenant

/2/billing get post

get

Get a list of billings.

post

Add a new billing.

get /2/billing

Get a list of billings.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: patientId, patientFirstName, patientLastName, patientAge, patientGender, employeeName, orderNo, invoiceNo, timestamp, status, content, billingCodes, treatCost, drugCost, matCost, totalCost. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • patientId: (string)
  • patientFirstName: (string)
  • patientLastName: (string)
  • patientAge: (number)
  • patientGender: (string)
  • employeeName: (string)
  • orderNo: (string)
  • invoiceNo: (string)
  • timestamp: (date)
  • status: (string)
  • content: (string)
  • billingCodes: (string)
  • treatCost: (number)
  • drugCost: (number)
  • matCost: (number)
  • totalCost: (number)

HTTP status code 400

Body

Type: application/json

Secured by basic

Secured by oauth2

Headers

  • Authorization: (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

/2/billing/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a billing

get

Get the billing with billingId = {billingId}

put

Update a specific billing using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

delete

Delete a specific billing.

get /2/billing/{_id}

Get the billing with billingId = {billingId}

Secured by oauth2

/2/blob

Collection of available blobs via REST /2.

/2/blob get post

get

Get a list of blobs.

post

Add a new blob.

get /2/blob

Get a list of blobs.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: ownerCollection, ownerId, transform, patientId, activityId, mediaId, dataURI, mimeType. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • ownerCollection: (string)
  • ownerId: (string)
  • transform: (string)
  • patientId: (string)
  • activityId: (string)
  • mediaId: (string)
  • dataURI: (string)
  • mimeType: (string)

Headers

  • Authorization: (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

Secured by JWT

Headers

  • Authorization: required (string)

    X-DC-App-Name

HTTP status code 401

HTTP status code 200

Body

Type: application/json

Example:

{
    "meta": {
        "errors": [],
        "warnings": [],
        "model": blob,
        "query": null,
        "itemsPerPage": null,
        "totalItems": 1,
        "page": null,
        "replyCode": 200
  },
  "data": [
     "54be764fc404c1d77a286d4d"
   ]
 }

HTTP status code 400

Body

Type: application/json

Secured by basic

Secured by oauth2

Headers

  • Authorization: (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

/2/blob/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a blob

get

Get the blob with blobId = {blobId}

put

Update a specific blob using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

delete

Delete a specific blob.

get /2/blob/{_id}

Get the blob with blobId = {blobId}

 }

HTTP status code 400

Body

Type: application/json

HTTP status code 404

Body

Type: application/json

Secured by basic

Secured by oauth2

Headers

  • Authorization: (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

put /2/blob/{_id}

Update a specific blob using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • _id: required (string)

HTTP status code 400

Body

Type: application/json

HTTP status code 404

Body

Type: application/json

Secured by basic

Secured by oauth2

Headers

  • Authorization: (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

delete /2/blob/{_id}

Delete a specific blob.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Body

Type: application/json

HTTP status code 403

Body

Type: application/json

HTTP status code 404

Body

Type: application/json

Secured by basic

Secured by oauth2

Headers

  • Authorization: (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

/2/calendar

Calendars.

/2/calendar get post

get

Get a list of calendars.

post

Add a new calendar.

get /2/calendar

Get a list of calendars.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: . Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'

HTTP status code 200

Body

Type: application/json

Schema:

{
  "type": "object",
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema",
  "id": "http://doccirrus.com/schema/calendar",
  "required": true,
  "properties": {
                      "name": {
                "type": "string",
                "required": true
      },
      "descr": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "Description"
      },
      "isPublic": {
                "type": "boolean",
                "description": "Is Public"
      },
      "isShared": {
                "type": "boolean"
      },
      "calGroup": {
                "type": {
                          "type": "array",
                          "items": {
                                    "type": "string"
                          }
                }
      },
      "isRandomMode": {
                "type": "boolean"
      },
      "type": {
                "enum": [
                          "INFORMAL",
                          "DUTIES",
                          "PATIENTS",
                          "INTRESOURCES",
                          "EXTRESOURCES"
                ]
      },
      "employee": {
                "type": "string"
      },
      "locationId": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "Location"
      },
      "color": {
                "type": "string",
                "required": true
      }
    }
              }

/2/calendar/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a calendar

get

Get the calendar with calendarId = {calendarId}

put

Update a specific calendar using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

delete

Delete a specific calendar.

/2/casefolder

Collection of available casefolders via REST /2.

The endpoint exposes special POST methods

  • Copy activities to specific casefolder in scope of the same patient.It requires to hand over a activitiesIds and target casefolderId. Other query parameters are free to choose. E.g.
    /2/casefolder/:copyActivitiesToCaseFolder 
    POST { activityIds:["5dfd3210b832a21249999234", "5dfd3210b832a21249999432"], caseFolderId:"5afd4c40b83294c249999999" }

/2/casefolder get post

get

Get a list of casefolders.

post

Add a new casefolder.

get /2/casefolder

Get a list of casefolders.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: patientId, type, additionalType, caseNumber, identity. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • patientId: (string)
  • type: (string)
  • additionalType: (string)
  • caseNumber: (string)
  • identity: (string)

HTTP status code 200

Body

Type: application/json

Schema:

{
  "type": "object",
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema",
  "id": "http://doccirrus.com/schema/casefolder",
  "required": true,
  "properties": {
                      "title": {
                "required": true
      },
      "start": {
                "type": "date"
      },
      "patientId": {
                "type": "string",
                "required": true
      },
      "type": {
                "description": "Invoice",
                "enum": [
                          "PUBLIC",
                          "PUBLIC_A",
                          "PRIVATE",
                          "PRIVATE_A",
                          "PRIVATE_CH",
                          "PRIVATE_CH_IVG",
                          "PRIVATE_CH_MVG",
                          "PRIVATE_CH_UVG",
                          "PRIVATE_CH_VVG",
                          "SELFPAYER",
                          "BG"
                ]
      },
      "additionalType": {
                "description": "Type",
                "enum": [
                          "QUOTATION",
                          "INCARE",
                          "FROM_PATIENT",
                          "DM1",
                          "DM2",
                          "BK",
                          "HGV",
                          "KHK",
                          "ASTHMA",
                          "COPD",
                          "HKS",
                          "ASV",
                          "CARDIO",
                          "DOQUVIDE",

                          "STROKE",
                          "CHD",
                          "PREGNANCY",
                          "ERROR",
                          "AMTS",
                          "ZERVIX_ZYTOLOGIE"
                ]
      },
      "caseNumber": {
                "type": "string"
      },
      "disabled": {
                "type": "boolean",
                "description": "deactivated"
      },
      "merged": {
                "type": "boolean"
      },
      "identity": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "type identity"
      }
    }
              }

{
  "meta": {
    "errors": [],

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • _id: required (string)

HTTP status code 200

Body

Type: application/json

Example:

{
  "meta": {
    "errors": [],
    "warnings": [],
    "query": {},
    "itemsPerPage": null,
    "totalItems": 1,
    "page": null,
    "replyCode": 200
  },
  "data": [
  {
    "emailTo": "email@example.com",
    "emailFrom": "testemail@example.com",
    "subject": "TEST Email",
    "text": "This is test email."
  }
]
 }

HTTP status code 400

Body

Type: application/json

HTTP status code 403

Body

Type: application/json

HTTP status code 404

Body

Type: application/json

Secured by basic

Secured by oauth2

Headers

  • Authorization: (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

/2/company

Collection of available companies via REST /2.

/2/company get post

get

Get a list of companies.

post

Add a new company.

get /2/company

Get a list of companies.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: cotype, deletedName, activeState. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • cotype: (string)
  • deletedName: (string)
  • activeState: (boolean)

HTTP status code 200

Body

Type: application/json

Example:

{
    "meta": {
        "errors": [],
        "warnings": [],
        "model": company,
        "query": null,
        "itemsPerPage": null,
        "totalItems": 1,
        "page": null,
        "replyCode": 200
  },
  "data": [
     "54be764fc404c1d77a286d4d"
   ]
 }

HTTP status code 400

Body

Type: application/json

Secured by basic

Secured by oauth2

Headers

  • Authorization: (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

/2/company/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a company

get

Get the company with companyId = {companyId}

put

Update a specific company using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

delete

Delete a specific company.

get /2/company/{_id}

Get the company with companyId = {companyId}

    true

    'field1,field2:1'

/2/contract

Collection of available contracts via REST /2.

The contract is needed for any sort of invoicing. The contract type provided specifies which insurance status of the patient is used SCHEIN - PUBLIC | PKVSCHEIN - PRIVATE | SZSCHEIN - SELFPAYER | BGSCHEIN - BG Note -- The SZSCHEIN psuedo-activity type for contracts. When this type is used, a SELFPAYER casefolder is added, although the contract is of type PKVSCHEIN.

The endpoint exposes special POST methods

  • Get all activities linked to a specific contract. It requires to hand over a patientId. Other query parameters are free to choose. E.g.
    /2/contract/:getLinkedActivities 
    POST { patientId:"5dfd3210b832a21249999234", _id:"5afd4c40b83294c249999999" }

/2/contract get post

get

Get a list of contracts.

post

Add a new contract.

get /2/contract

Get a list of contracts.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: actType, status, activityId, subType, timestamp, patientId, locationId, mirrorCaseFolderType, formId, formVersion, caseFolderId, patientName, invoiceLogId, invoiceLogType, caseNumber, checkProcessId. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • actType: (string)
  • status: (string)
  • activityId: (string)
  • subType: (string)
  • timestamp: (date)
  • patientId: (string)
  • locationId: (string)
  • mirrorCaseFolderType: (string)
  • formId: (string)
  • formVersion: (string)
  • caseFolderId: (string)
  • patientName: (string)
  • invoiceLogId: (string)
  • invoiceLogType: (string)
  • caseNumber: (string)
  • checkProcessId: (string)

/2/contract/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a contract

get

Get the contract with contractId = {contractId}

put

Update a specific contract using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

/2/diagnosis

Collection of available diagnoses via REST /2.

The endpoint exposes special POST methods

  • Get all diagnoses linked to a specific contract. It requires to hand over a patientId. Other query parameters are free to choose. E.g.
    /2/diagnosis/:getActivitiesLinkedToContract 
    POST { patientId:"5dfd3210b832a21249999234", _id:"5afd4c40b83294c249999999" }

/2/diagnosis get post

get

Get a list of diagnoses.

post

Add a new diagnosis.

get /2/diagnosis

Get a list of diagnoses.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: status, subType, timestamp, patientId, locationId, mirrorCaseFolderType, formId, formVersion, caseFolderId, patientName, code. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • status: (string)
  • subType: (string)
  • timestamp: (date)
  • patientId: (string)
  • locationId: (string)
  • mirrorCaseFolderType: (string)
  • formId: (string)
  • formVersion: (string)
  • caseFolderId: (string)
  • patientName: (string)
  • code: (string)

/2/diagnosis/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a diagnosis

get

Get the diagnosis with diagnosisId = {diagnosisId}

put

Update a specific diagnosis using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

/2/dispatchrequest

The dispatcher request sends a limited collection of activities to the dispatcher for further routing.The allowed types are listed in the JSON Schema definition. This API has no effect on data safes, or MVPRC servers.

/2/dispatchrequest get post

get

Get a list of dispatchrequests.

post

Add a new dispatchrequest.

get /2/dispatchrequest

Get a list of dispatchrequests.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: bsnr, lanr. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • bsnr: (string)
  • lanr: (string)

HTTP status code 200

/2/dispatchrequest/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a dispatchrequest

get

Get the dispatchrequest with dispatchrequestId = {dispatchrequestId}

put

Update a specific dispatchrequest using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

/2/document

Provides access to the documents collection.

/2/document get post

get

Get a list of documents.

post

Add a new document.

get /2/document

Get a list of documents.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: patientId, activityId, mediaId. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • patientId: (string)
  • activityId: (string)
  • mediaId: (string)

Headers

  • Authorization: (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

/2/ingredientplan

Create Ingredient Plan with some med data items

/2/ingredientplan get post

get

Get a list of ingredientplans.

post

Add a new ingredientplan.

get /2/ingredientplan

Get a list of ingredientplans.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: subType, timestamp, patientId, locationId, mirrorCaseFolderType, formId, formVersion, caseFolderId, patientName. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • subType: (string)
  • timestamp: (date)
  • patientId: (string)
  • locationId: (string)
  • mirrorCaseFolderType: (string)
  • formId: (string)
  • formVersion: (string)
  • caseFolderId: (string)
  • patientName: (string)

/2/ingredientplan/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a ingredientplan

get

Get the ingredientplan with ingredientplanId = {ingredientplanId}

put

Update a specific ingredientplan using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

delete

Delete a specific ingredientplan.

Headers

  • Authorization: (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

/2/invoice

Returns all requested invoice activity types. When an invoice is posted into the system using this method in v.4.0, additional manual intervention is still required to create a PDF for the invoice and get an invoice number from the system.

/2/invoice get post

get

Get a list of invoices.

post

Add a new invoice.

get /2/invoice

Get a list of invoices.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: status, subType, timestamp, patientId, locationId, mirrorCaseFolderType, formId, formVersion, caseFolderId, patientName, invoiceDate, invoiceBilledDate. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • status: (string)
  • subType: (string)
  • timestamp: (date)
  • patientId: (string)
  • locationId: (string)
  • mirrorCaseFolderType: (string)
  • formId: (string)
  • formVersion: (string)
  • caseFolderId: (string)
  • patientName: (string)
  • invoiceDate: (date)
  • invoiceBilledDate: (date)

/2/invoice/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a invoice

get

Get the invoice with invoiceId = {invoiceId}

put

Update a specific invoice using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

delete

Delete a specific invoice.

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

put /2/invoice/{_id}

Update a specific invoice using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

/2/kbvmedicationplan

Medicationplan activity

/2/kbvmedicationplan get post

get

Get a list of kbvmedicationplans.

post

Add a new kbvmedicationplan.

get /2/kbvmedicationplan

Get a list of kbvmedicationplans.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: subType, timestamp, patientId, locationId, mirrorCaseFolderType, formId, formVersion, caseFolderId, patientName. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • subType: (string)
  • timestamp: (date)
  • patientId: (string)
  • locationId: (string)
  • mirrorCaseFolderType: (string)
  • formId: (string)
  • formVersion: (string)
  • caseFolderId: (string)
  • patientName: (string)

Entity representing a kbvmedicationplan

get

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

HTTP status code 400

Body

Type: application/json

HTTP status code 404

Body

Type: application/json

Secured by basic

Secured by oauth2

Headers

  • Authorization: (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

put /2/kbvmedicationplan/{_id}

Update a specific kbvmedicationplan using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

HTTP status code 403

Body

Type: application/json

HTTP status code 404

Body

Type: application/json

Secured by basic

Secured by oauth2

Headers

  • Authorization: (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

/2/labdata

Collection of available labdata via REST /2.

The endpoint exposes special POST methods

  • Get all labdata linked to a specific contract. It requires to hand over a patientId. Other query parameters are free to choose. E.g.
    /2/labdata/:getActivitiesLinkedToContract 
    POST { patientId:"5dfd3210b832a21249999234", _id:"5afd4c40b83294c249999999" }

/2/labdata get post

get

Get a list of labdata.

post

Add a new labdatum.

get /2/labdata

Get a list of labdata.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: status, subType, timestamp, patientId, locationId, mirrorCaseFolderType, formId, formVersion, caseFolderId, patientName, labLogTimestamp. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • status: (string)
  • subType: (string)
  • timestamp: (date)
  • patientId: (string)
  • locationId: (string)
  • mirrorCaseFolderType: (string)
  • formId: (string)
  • formVersion: (string)
  • caseFolderId: (string)
  • patientName: (string)
  • labLogTimestamp: (date)

HTTP status code 200

Body

Type: application/json

Schema:

{
  "type": "object",
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema",
  "id": "http://doccirrus.com/schema/labdata",
  "required": true,
  "properties": {
                      "actType": {
                "enum": [
                          "LABDATA"
                ],
                "required": true
      },
      "labEntries": {
                "type": "object",
                "description": "Simplified Lab Data"
      },
      "status": {
                "type": "string",
                "description": "The status of an activity is read-only. Using this parameter in POST / PUT has no effect."
      },
      "attachments": {
                "type": {
                          "type": "array",
                          "items": {
                                    "type": "string"
                          }
                }
      },
      "attachedMediaTags": {
                "type": {
                          "type": "array",
                          "items": {
                                    "type": "string"
                          }
                },
                "description": "Tags"
      },
      "subType": {
                "type": "string",

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

/2/labdata/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a labdatum

get

Get the labdatum with labdatumId = {labdatumId}

put

Update a specific labdatum using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

/2/location

Collection of available locations via REST /2.

/2/location get post

get

Get a list of locations.

post

Add a new location.

get /2/location

Get a list of locations.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: city, receiver, payerType, firstname, lastname, cantonCode. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • city: (string)
  • receiver: (string)
  • payerType: (string)
  • firstname: (string)
  • lastname: (string)
  • cantonCode: (string)

/2/location/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a location

get

Get the location with locationId = {locationId}

put

Update a specific location using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

/2/meddata

Collection of activities of actType MEDDATA (or relatives of these) via REST /2.

Each activity contains an array of items inside medData, which may be used to store structured content under an item's type. An item provides a separate field for each generic data type, and can store a numeric value in value, a string value in textValue, a boolean value in boolValue, and a date value in dateValue. The content inside these properties is validated against the collection of tags of type MEDDATA (see /2/tag for further details). In case the type is not found among the existing tags or among the list of static tags, the first item of that type pushed to the interface will create a new tag. If this is not wanted the noTagCreation flag may be set on the item (i.e. if the type will likely not be re-used in the future). The new tag will contain a new validation configuration fixing the structure of any item of the same type being posted to the API in the future. I.e. if the new item contains only a textValue, any item of the same type which is pushed in the future needs to contain a textValue, or will get rejected.

Example 1
No MEDDATA tag exists with title:'EXAMPLE1'. The first request made to /2/meddata posts

{actType:"MEDDATA", ..., medData:[{ type:"EXAMPLE1", textValue:"test" }]}
A second requests tries to post
{actType:"MEDDATA", ..., medData:[{ type:"EXAMPLE1", value:123456 }]}
The second request will get rejected as no textValue is set on the item. A query to /2/tag will return a tag which prevents the second request to succeed.
{type:"MEDDATA", title:"EXAMPLE1", ..., medDataItemConfig:[{ dataType:"STRING", validFromIncl:"DATE_OF_FIRST_REQUEST" }]}


Example 2
No MEDDATA tag exists with title:'EXAMPLE2'. The first request made to /2/meddata posts
{actType:"MEDDATA", ..., medData:[{ type:"EXAMPLE2", textValue:"test", noTagCreation:true }]}
A second requests tries to post
{actType:"MEDDATA", ..., medData:[{ type:"EXAMPLE2", value:123456, noTagCreation:true }]}
The second request will succeed as the flag noTagCreation was set on the first item. Hence, a query to /2/tag returns no tag with title:'EXAMPLE2', and the second request is not validated against any tag.

Additional functions exposed on this endpoint:
  • Get all activities linked to a specific contract. Required parameters are patientId and _id of the contract. Other query parameters are free to choose. E.g.
    /2/meddata/:getActivitiesLinkedToContract 
    POST { patientId:"5dfd3210b832a21249999234", _id:"5afd4c40b83294c249999999" }

/2/meddata get post

get

Get a list of meddata.

post

Add a new meddatum.

get /2/meddata

Get a list of meddata.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: subType, timestamp, patientId, locationId, mirrorCaseFolderType, formId, formVersion, caseFolderId, patientName, medDataType. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • subType: (string)
  • timestamp: (date)
  • patientId: (string)
  • locationId: (string)
  • mirrorCaseFolderType: (string)
  • formId: (string)
  • formVersion: (string)
  • caseFolderId: (string)
  • patientName: (string)
  • medDataType: (string)

    Allows the request to filter by medData type

HTTP status code 200

Body

Type: application/json

Schema:

{
  "type": "object",
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema",
  "id": "http://doccirrus.com/schema/meddata",
  "required": true,
  "properties": {
                      "actType": {
                "enum": [
                          "MEDDATA",
                          "GRAVIDOGRAMMPROCESS",
                          "PERCENTILECURVE",
                          "GRAVIDOGRAMM"
                ],
                "required": true
      },
      "attachments": {
                "type": {
                          "type": "array",
                          "items": {
                                    "type": "string"
                          }

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

/2/meddata/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a meddatum

get

Get the meddatum with meddatumId = {meddatumId}

put

Update a specific meddatum using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

delete

/2/medication

Collection of available medications via REST /2.

The endpoint exposes special POST methods

  • Get all medications linked to a specific contract. It requires to hand over a patientId. Other query parameters are free to choose. E.g.
    /2/medication/:getActivitiesLinkedToContract 
    POST { patientId:"5dfd3210b832a21249999234", _id:"5afd4c40b83294c249999999" }

/2/medication get post

get

Get a list of medications.

post

Add a new medication.

get /2/medication

Get a list of medications.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: subType, timestamp, patientId, locationId, mirrorCaseFolderType, formId, formVersion, caseFolderId, patientName, restRequestId, code. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • subType: (string)
  • timestamp: (date)
  • patientId: (string)
  • locationId: (string)
  • mirrorCaseFolderType: (string)
  • formId: (string)
  • formVersion: (string)
  • caseFolderId: (string)
  • patientName: (string)
  • restRequestId: (string)
  • code: (string)

/2/medication/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a medication

get

Get the medication with medicationId = {medicationId}

put

Update a specific medication using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

/2/partneridcatalog

Applications can register themselves in the patient care section. A typical workflow is as follows:
/2/partneridcatalog is extended with a new unique code
 a license with this code is granted to the datasafe in question
* now users see the section and name in the patient info, and the information flows into the patient.partnerIds array.

/2/partneridcatalog get post

get

Get a list of partneridcatalogs.

post

Add a new partneridcatalog.

get /2/partneridcatalog

Get a list of partneridcatalogs.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: code, name. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • code: (string)
  • name: (string)

HTTP status code 200

Body

Type: application/json

Schema:

{
  "type": "object",
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema",
  "id": "http://doccirrus.com/schema/partneridcatalog",
  "required": true,
  "properties": {
                      "code": {
                "required": true,
                "type": "string"
      },
      "name": {
                "required": true,
                "type": "string"
      }
    }
              }

Example:

{
  "meta": {
    "errors": [],
    "warnings": [],
    "query": {},
    "itemsPerPage": null,
    "totalItems": 1,
    "page": null,
    "replyCode": 200
  },
  "data": [

/2/partneridcatalog/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a partneridcatalog

get

Get the partneridcatalog with partneridcatalogId = {partneridcatalogId}

put

Update a specific partneridcatalog using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

/2/patient

The patient collection holds all data relevant to a patient, including all insurance data.
The patient endpoint exposes a JSON RPC method for getting a patient from a specific cardreader instead of the DB. e.g.

 /2/patient/:readCard?_id=5afd4c40b83294c249999999
See also /2/cardreader

/2/patient get post

get

Get a list of patients.

post

Add a new patient.

get /2/patient

Get a list of patients.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: firstname, lastname, activeState, dob, patientNo, socialSecurityNo, amtsSelectiveContractInsuranceId. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • firstname: (string)
  • lastname: (string)
  • activeState: (boolean)
  • dob: (date)
  • patientNo: (string)
  • socialSecurityNo: (string)
  • amtsSelectiveContractInsuranceId: (string)

HTTP status code 400

Body

Type: application/json

Secured by basic

Secured by oauth2

Headers

  • Authorization: (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

Secured by JWT

Headers

  • Authorization: required (string)

    X-DC-App-Name

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user revokes the solution's access. The user

post /2/patient

Add a new patient.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

  • Response

HTTP status code 200

Body

Type: application/json

Example:

{
    "meta": {
        "errors": [],
        "warnings": [],
        "model": patient,
        "query": null,
        "itemsPerPage": null,
        "totalItems": 1,
        "page": null,
        "replyCode": 200
  },
  "data": [
     "54be764fc404c1d77a286d4d"
   ]
 }

HTTP status code 400

Body

Type: application/json

Secured by basic

Secured by oauth2

Headers

  • Authorization: (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

/2/patient/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a patient

get

Get the patient with patientId = {patientId}

put

Update a specific patient using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

delete

Delete a specific patient.

get /2/patient/{_id}

Get the patient with patientId = {patientId}

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

URI Parameters

  • _id: required (string)

put /2/patient/{_id}

Update a specific patient using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Body

Type: application/json

Secured by basic

Secured by oauth2

Headers

  • Authorization: (string)

    Used to send a valid OAuth 2 access token. Do not use with the "access_token" query string parameter.

HTTP status code 401

Bad or expired token. This can happen if the user or Doc Cirrus revoked or expired an access token. To fix, you should re- authenticate the user.

HTTP status code 403

Bad OAuth request (wrong consumer key, bad nonce, expired timestamp...). Unfortunately, re-authenticating the user won't help here.

/2/patient/{_id}/partnerIds/{_id} put delete

Access an individual partnerId within a parent document. The parent document must be specified by Id before using the sub-document (collection). Use this to either update the individual sub-document, or to delete it.

put

Update a specific partnerId. You must use the ID of the record.

delete

Delete a specific partnerId.

put /2/patient/{_id}/partnerIds/{_id}

Update a specific partnerId. You must use the ID of the record.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

  • Response
  • Security

  • _id: required (string)
  • _id: required (string)

/2/physician

Collection of available physicians via REST /2.

/2/physician get post

get

Get a list of physicians.

post

Add a new physician.

get /2/physician

Get a list of physicians.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: baseContactType, firstname, lastname, officialNo. Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'
  • baseContactType: (string)
  • firstname: (string)
  • lastname: (string)
  • officialNo: (string)

/2/physician/{_id} get put delete

Entity representing a physician

get

Get the physician with physicianId = {physicianId}

put

Update a specific physician using the ID of the record.

Notes

  • The entire resource must always be submitted with a put.

  • For parts of the resource which are lists (JSON arrays) of information (e.g. addresses, communications, or opening times), you can remove members from the list by putting the entire new list.

delete

Delete a specific physician.

get /2/physician/{_id}

Get the physician with physicianId = {physicianId}

/2/role

Roles available for the Praxis. For v.2. we only allow get

/2/role get post

get

Get a list of roles.

post

Add a new role.

get /2/role

Get a list of roles.

Secured by basic
Secured by oauth2

Doc Cirrus supports OAuth 2.0 for authenticating all API requests. Authorisation service is provided by partner.

Secured by JWT

Solutions have the possibility of using a JWT based authentication mechanism to interact with /2. A token is issued by DC and has to be activated by each individual datasafe.

  • Request
  • Response
  • Security

Query Parameters

  • page: (integer - default: 0)

    Skip over a number of pages by specifying an offset value for the query

    Example:

    20
  • itemsPerPage: (integer - default: 1000)

    Limit the number of elements on the response

    Example:

    80
  • noCountLimit: (string - default: false)

    Pageable results return the totalItems field which is the count of collection which is limited to 2001. If this parameter is set to 'true', then the total count is returned.

    Example:

    true
  • sort: (string)

    Sort the result list by field: . Fields are comma-separated and can accept a value if followed by a colon mark (see example).

    Example:

    'field1,field2:1'

HTTP status code 200

Body

Type: application/json

Schema:

{
  "type": "object",
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema",
  "id": "http://doccirrus.com/schema/role",
  "required": true,
  "properties": {
                      "value": {
                "type": "string",
                "required": true
      }
    }
              }

Example:

{
  "meta": {
    "errors": [],
    "warnings": [],
    "query": {"_id":"000000000000000000000001"},
    "itemsPerPage": null,
    "totalItems": 1,
    "page": null,
    "replyCode": 200
  },
  "data": [
  {
    "_id": "000000000000000000000001",
    "value": "Empfang"
  }
]
 }
